title: Facebook’s New Role as News Publisher Brings New Scrutiny
text: A quarrel arises over a newsletter’s attempt to tie Campbell Brown, Facebook’s news head, to articles attacking Elizabeth Warren on a website she co-founded.

title: Facebook machine learning aims to modify faces, hands, and… outfits
text: The latest research out of Facebook sets machine learning models to tasks that, to us, seem rather ordinary — but for a computer are still monstrously difficult.

title: Facebook finally lets you banish nav bar tabs & red dots
text: Are those red notification dots on your Facebook home screen driving you crazy? Sick of Facebook Marketplace wasting your screen space?

title: There's a race to replace our iPhones with smart glasses we wear everywhere
text: Microsoft, Snap, Facebook, Google, Apple and Amazon are all racing to replace our phones with glasses we wear everywhere.

title: There could be a simple solution to Facebook’s political ad woes
text: David Carroll, professor and star of the Netflix doc ‘The Great Hack,’ argues that microtargeted political ads pervert the democratic process. What if Facebook just disabled them?
